OL,3,CMan died hours after being escorted
OL,4,Coff a plane in Turkey
OL,6,FHe died a few hours later, in the
OL,7,Fearly hours of 25 September, after
OL,8,F"falling from a height", with coroner
OL,9,FCaroline Saunders confirming the
OL,10,Fincident to be an accident with "no
OL,11,Fevidence of third party involvement or
OL,12,Fthat he jumped."
OL,14,FA post-mortem examination carried out
OL,15,Frevealed Mr Crook had suffered a
OL,16,Ffractured skull and pelvis caused by
OL,17,Fblunt trauma.
OL,19,FThe court heard that Mr Crook was a
OL,20,F"nervous flier" but had been "chatting
OL,21,Fand joking" before take-off.
